HEADWORD: Geodesy
<hw>Ge*od"e*sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>ge`a</grk>, <grk>gh^</grk>, the earth + <?/ to divide: cf. F.
<ets>g⟦eacute⟧od⟦eacute⟧sie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>That
branch of applied mathematics which determines, by means of observations
and measurements, the figures and areas of large portions of the earth's
surface, or the general figure and dimensions of the earth; or that
branch of surveying in which the curvature of the earth is taken into
account, as in the surveys of States, or of long lines of
coast.</def></p>

